****
This solution employs a stack to keep track of equal adjacent letters. Time complexity is linear: **O(N)**. Space complexity is linear: **O(N)**.

**Comment.** To remove adjacent duplicates, we iteratively compare each letter with the last letter on the stack. This problem is almost identical to the November 8th's daily challenge [**1544. Make The String Great**](https://leetcode.com/problems/make-the-string-great/) (check my [**solution**](https://leetcode.com/problems/make-the-string-great/discuss/2790965/PythonC%2B%2BJavaRust-Make-The-String-Great-Again-(explained))).

