solutions.content:
We can use two-pointer method to solve this problem. We can set a pointer p to point the next index of current substring:
**1. If there are no 2 same adjacent characters, then we move p forward along with i;
2. else, we move back for 1 step since we need to remove those 2 same adjacent characters!**

```
    public String removeDuplicates(String S) {
        char[] ch = S.toCharArray();
        int len = S.length(), p = 0; // p as a pointer, to point the next index of current substring.
        for (int i=0; i<len; i++) {
            if (p == 0 || ch[i] != ch[p-1]) {
                ch[p++] = ch[i];
            } else {
                p--;
            }
        }
        return String.valueOf(ch).substring(0, p);
    }
```

