solutions.content:
We create an output array the new string will be written to, we have a variable that tracks our position in the output. We loop through the chars in the input string, if the char equal that last value in the output array, then we skip the char and decrement the position variable to 'delete' the last char.

```
public class Solution {
    public string RemoveDuplicates(string S) {

        char[] output = new char[S.Length];
        int position = -1;

        for (int i = 0; i < S.Length; i++){
            if (position >= 0 && S[i] == output[position]){
                position--;
            }
            else{
                output[++position] = S[i];
            }
        }

        return new string(output.Take(position + 1).ToArray());
    }
}
```

