I haven't seen any solutions with regex and replace so I figured I would share mine. It took 52ms and used 36.5MB of memory.

```
var removeDuplicates = function(S) {
    const regex = /(.)\1/gm;
    let startLength;

    do {
        startLength = S.length;
        S = S.replace(regex, '');
    } while (S.length != startLength);

    return S;
};
```

