Simple functional solution with windows (effective with small window):
```
impl Solution {
    pub fn three_consecutive_odds(arr: Vec<i32>) -> bool {
        arr.windows(3)
            .map(|v| v.iter().all(|x| *x % 2 == 1))
            .any(|x| x)
    }
}
```

Much effective solution with simple cycle and counter (we calc remainder only once for each value in vector):
```
impl Solution {
    pub fn three_consecutive_odds(arr: Vec<i32>) -> bool {
        let mut n_odds = 0;
        for is_odd in arr.iter().map(|x| *x % 2 == 1) {
            match is_odd {
                true => {
                    n_odds += 1;
                    if n_odds == 3 {
                        return true;
                    }
                }
                false => n_odds = 0,
            }
        }
        false
    }
}
```

