solutions.content:
This question is same as question **Super Egg Drop** instead of k identical egg we have given 2 identical eggs.
For every floor there will be two cases :
*  Egg will break between 1-st to n-th floor, let say k-th floor.
*  Egg will break after k-th floor, means between (n-k)th to n-th floor.

We will take maximum of these two cases for every floor and store the minimum possible value among these maximum values in dp.

**Java Implementation**
```
class Solution {
    public int twoEggDrop(int n) {
        int[] dp = new int[n+1];
        dp[0] = 0;
        dp[1] = 1;
        for(int i=2 ; i<dp.length ; i++){
            dp[i] = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
            for(int k=1 ; k<=i ; k++){
			//Taking max between two possible cases.
                max = 1 + Math.max(k-1, dp[i - k]);
                if(max < dp[i]){
				//Taking minimum of all max values
                    dp[i] = max;
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

**C++ Implementation**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int twoEggDrop(int n) {
        int dp[n + 1];
        dp[0] = 0;
        dp[1] = 1;
        for(int i=2 ; i<n+1 ; i++){
            dp[i] = INT_MAX;
            int val = INT_MIN;
            for(int k=1 ; k<=i ; k++){
			//Taking max between two possible cases.
                val = 1 + max(k-1, dp[i - k]);
                if(val < dp[i]){
				//Taking minimum of all max values
                    dp[i] = val;
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n];
    }
};
```
**Time Complexity : O(n^2)
Space Complexity : O(n).**

