```
Suppose there are 20 floors, 
Floors to check with egg 1 : 6 , 11, 15, 18, 20. 

If the egg-break floor is between 1 and 6 inclusive, 
Max chances = 1(6th floor) + 5(1st to 5th floor incrementally) = 6.

If the egg-break floor is between 6 and 11 inclusive, 
Max chances = 1(6th floor) + 1(11th floor) + 4(7 to 10th floor incrementally) = 6

If the egg-break floor is between 11 and 15 inclusive, 
Max chances = 1(6th floor) + 1(11th floor) + 1(15th floor)  +3(12 to 14th floor incrementally) 
= 6.

Hence we are always reaching the egg-break floor in at most 6 moves. 
```

