solutions.content:
Inspired by @lee215's solution on k eggs, n floors, we can think in different way that given 2 eggs, we want to find the maximum floors we can test. If it is more than required n, we can return the moves.
TC: O(n) SC: O(n)
```
class Solution {
    public int twoEggDrop(int n) {   
        // given x steps, the maximum floors I can test with two eggs
        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            // move is i, previous move is i - 1,
            // we put egg on floor i, if egg breaks, we can check i - 1 floors with i - 1 moves
            // if egg does not break, we can check dp[i-1] floors having two eggs to with i - 1 moves
            dp[i] = 1 + i - 1 + dp[i - 1];
            if (dp[i] >= n) {
                return i;
            }
        }
        return 0;
    }
}
```

