solutions.content:
If we drop the egg on floor i, there are 2 scenarios:
- the egg broke, then we continue with `floor[0...i-1]` with `(k - 1)` eggs
- the egg does not break, we continue with `floor[i...n-1]` with k eggs

`dp(i, k)` means  the worst scenario to determine centain f by dropping k eggs with i floors

```
dp(i, k) = MAX(dp(i - 1, k - 1),  if egg breaks
                dp(n - i, k))     if egg does not break
```
Take the minimum of trying all the possible floor i to start dropping.

Base Case:
- `k == 1`, then we need to test all remaining floors
- `n == 0`, no more floors

```
class Solution {
    Integer[][] memo;
    public int twoEggDrop(int n) {
        int k = 2;
        memo = new Integer[n + 1][k + 1];
        return helper(n, k);
    }

    private int helper(int n, int k){
        if(n == 0) return 0;
        if(k == 1) return n;
        if(memo[n][k] != null) return memo[n][k];
        int res = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            res = Math.min(res, 1 + Math.max(helper(i - 1, k - 1), helper(n - i, k)));
        }
        return memo[n][k] = res;
    }
}
```

