# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The Problem is a series question where dropping an egg takes place from flores with difference of 1,2,3,4,....upto the 1st floor.

say n=100
Here 100 are there , so dropping of an egg takes place from 100, 99, 97, 94,.....9

upon close looking 100, 99, 97, 94, 90, 85,.....
the diiference in floor numbers is 1,2,3,4,5,....

So the maximum drops possible is counting of floor numbers till f>=1.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
declare a var c for counting of floors.
iterate a loop with i=1.
    substract the i from n till n>0 and the no of times the loop iterated.
        if(n>0)
            n=n-i
            c=c+1;
return c value.

